  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Mycorrhiza (plural: mycorrhizae): a symbiotic association between a fungus and the roots of a plant. The term means literally \u0026ldquo;fungus-root\u0026rdquo; (Greek mykes + rhiza). In a mycorrhizal association, the fungal mycelium extends from the plant\u0026rsquo;s root system into the surrounding soil, vastly increasing the surface area available for nutrient and water absorption. The plant gains enhanced mineral nutrition — especially phosphorus, which is poorly mobile in soil — and the fungus gains photosynthetically fixed carbon from the plant.\n",
  "keywords": "mycology, symbiosis, plant-fungal-interaction",
  "name": "Mycorrhiza",
